# Git Workflow

## Branch Protection

- **NEVER push to `master`.** It is protected and requires PRs with passing status checks.
- Do not even attempt `git push origin master` — it will be rejected and wastes time.
- Always create a feature branch, commit there, push, and open a PR via `gh pr create`.

## Branch Naming

- Feature work: `feature/<short-description>` (e.g., `feature/job-pool-option-a`)
- Research/docs: `research/<short-description>`
- Bug fixes: `fix/<short-description>`

## Commits

- Pull `master` before branching: `git checkout master && git pull && git checkout -b <branch>`.
- Run `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` (in both Debug and Release configurations) before
  committing. Fix any violations.
- Run `dotnet test` and confirm zero test failures before pushing. The pre-existing
  `System.InvalidOperationException: A test session start event` error is a known infrastructure
  bug — ignore the exit code if all tests pass with `failed: 0`.
